HEADWORD: Conjunctiva
<hw>Con`junc*ti"va</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
L. <ets>conjunctivus</ets> connective.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>The mucous membrane which covers the external surface of the ball
of the eye and the inner surface of the lids; the conjunctival
membrane.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

